info.headline: Wind Advisory issued August 19 at 2:16AM MST until August 20 at 10:00PM MST by NWS Tucson
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 11 AM TO 10 PM MST SUNDAY... * WHAT...South to southeast winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts 45-50 mph. The strongest sustained winds will occur in the higher terrain. The strongest wind gusts in the lower deserts will accompany showers and thunderstorms. * WHERE...Western Pima County, Tohono O`odham Nation and Baboquivari Mountains. * WHEN...From 11 AM to 10 PM MST Sunday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
